<section xmlns   ="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
         xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
         xml:id  ="use-authn"
         xml:lang="en"
         version ="5.0">
  <title>Authentication</title>
  <para>
    Clients authenticate to the SCIM APIs by using bearer token authentication, as defined by <link xl:show="new" xl:href="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6750" xl:role="http://docbook.org/xlink/role/olink"><citetitle>RFC 6750</citetitle></link>.
    Every request must include an Authorization request header, where the header value uses the form <literal>Bearer {access token}</literal>
  </para>
  <para>
    A bearer token must be obtained from an external authorization server, such as Oracle Access Manager.
  </para>
</section>